Detailed Description

The section has a list of all function which need to be populated by a developers writing a custom profile to fit with the Test Framework.

Typedef Documentation

typedef void(* TestFmk_ProfileChirpAvailableCallbackFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is invoked once the chirp available interrupt has been detected

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the profile
Return values
Notapplicable
typedef int32_t(* TestFmk_ProfileCloseFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is used to close the profile.

Parameters
[in]handleProfile handle
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
typedef int32_t(* TestFmk_ProfileControlFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle, uint32_t cmd, void *arg, uint32_t argLen, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is used to control the profile. Profile developers can use this to provide the ability to provide additional control capability. The "cmd" for profiles should be offset by TEST_FMK_CMD_PROFILE_START_INDEX to prevent an overlap with the TestFmk commands.

In addition to the profile specific commands the following commands should also be handled:-

See also
TEST_FMK_CMD_NOTIFY_FAULT
Parameters
[in]handleProfile handle
[in]cmdCommand to be processed
[in]argCommand specific argument.
[in]argLenCommand specific argument length
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
typedef int32_t(* TestFmk_ProfileDeinitFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is used to deinitialize the profile and this is invoked during the TestFmk Deinitialization process.

Parameters
[in]handleProfile handle
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
typedef int32_t(* TestFmk_ProfileExecuteFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle, TestFmk_Result *ptrResult, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is used to execute the profile The profile is woken up on the reception of a chirp interrupt

Parameters
[in]handleProfile handle
[out]ptrResultPointer to the result populated by the profile
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
typedef int32_t(* TestFmk_ProfileFinalizeCfgFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle, TestFmk_Cfg *ptrTestFmkCfg, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is invoked by the framework to finalize all the configuration. The profile

  • MAY NOT* support any configuration modifications after the invocation of this function.
Parameters
[in]handleProfile handle
[in]ptrTestFmkCfgPointer to the TestFmk configuration
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

typedef TestFmk_ProfileHandle(* TestFmk_ProfileInitFxn) (TestFmk_Handle fmkHandle, TestFmk_InitCfg *ptrInitCfg, SemaphoreP_Handle fmkSemHandle, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is used to initialize and setup the profile. This is invoked during the TestFmk Initialization process. Profiles are required to initialize and setup any of the modules which are required

Parameters
[in]fmkHandleHandle to the TestFmk Module loading the profile
[in]ptrInitCfgPointer to the initialization configuration
[in]fmkSemHandleHandle to the framework semaphore.
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- Handle to the profile
Error- <0
typedef int32_t(* TestFmk_ProfileOpenFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle, MMWave_OpenCfg *ptrOpenCfg, int32_t *errCode)

typedef int32_t(* TestFmk_ProfileStartFxn) (TestFmk_ProfileHandle handle, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the profile registered function which is used to start the profile. Profiles should be started before the sensor (BSS) is started. Profiles will use this to setup and prepare itself to start receiving ADC samples

Parameters
[in]handleProfile handle
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
